Defendant in custody.   
Count 1 - Bail Jumping as repeater - Guilty plea.   
Count 4 - Burglary as repeater - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2, 3, 5, and 6.  Motion granted.   Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years on each count, concurrent and concurrent with Case No. 15 CF 525.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Continue with his mental health treatment;
3) Take all medications as prescribed and in prescribed doses;
4) AODA assessment and follow through; 
5) Maintain full-time work and/or job search combination; 
6) Have no contact with Rahr West Museum, St. John's United Church of Christ, St. Vincent DePaul, Stephanie Bowman and Diane Murray;
7) Pay costs of action; 
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
9) Submit DNA sample.   
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  
Defendant is given credit for 134 days time already served.   
Minutes.
